{"history":[{"role":"user","content":"Who is eligible for Disability Support Pension?","timestamp":"2026-02-23T02:58:12.438Z"},{"role":"assistant","content":"To be eligible for the Disability Support Pension (DSP), a claimant must meet both non-medical and medical criteria:\n\n### Non-Medical Eligibility Criteria:\n1. **Age**: The claimant must be aged at least 15 years and 9 months and under the Age Pension age when claiming.\n2. **Residence**: The disability must have occurred while living in Australia or New Zealand, and the claimant must have lived in Australia for more than 10 years.\n3. **Income and Assets**: The claimant must meet specific income and assets tests.\n\n### Medical Eligibility Criteria:\n1. The claimant must have a physical, intellectual, or psychiatric impairment that prevents them from working.\n2. The impairment must be permanent and have persisted for more than 2 years.\n3. Alternatively, the claimant may meet manifest eligibility criteria, such as being permanently blind.\n\nAdditionally, some individuals may be required to participate in a Program of Support (POS) unless they meet certain medical rules or have a specific impairment rating [Source 1][Source 4][Source 5][Source 6]. \n\nFor more detailed information, you can visit the Services Australia website or contact them directly.","timestamp":"2026-02-23T02:58:12.438Z","sources":[{"index":1,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-12--co029-2601.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2025-12/co029-2601.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.20686459907934468},{"index":2,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-03--co029-2503.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2025-03/co029-2503.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2471344623995621},{"index":3,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2023-10--aus140-2310nz.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2023-10/aus140-2310nz.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.29339147227037005},{"index":4,"file":"payments/who-can-get-disability-support-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-disability-support-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.30003253998896573},{"index":5,"file":"general/program-support-for-disability-support-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/program-support-for-disability-support-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3146460706263408},{"index":6,"file":"general/get-centrelink-payment.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/get-centrelink-payment","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3350189601917966},{"index":7,"file":"payments/who-can-get-utilities-allowance.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-utilities-allowance","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.33711417882190503},{"index":8,"file":"general/income-and-assets-tests-for-disability-support-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/income-and-assets-tests-for-disability-support-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.34540219063499583}],"memoryId":"mem-4c348898-1771815492438"}],"memories":[{"id":"mem-4c348898-1771815492438","query":"Who is eligible for Disability Support Pension?","answer":"To be eligible for the Disability Support Pension (DSP), a claimant must meet both non-medical and medical criteria:\n\n### Non-Medical Eligibility Criteria:\n1. **Age**: The claimant must be aged at least 15 years and 9 months and under the Age Pension age when claiming.\n2. **Residence**: The disability must have occurred while living in Australia or New Zealand, and the claimant must have lived in Australia for more than 10 years.\n3. **Income and Assets**: The claimant must meet specific income and assets tests.\n\n### Medical Eligibility Criteria:\n1. The claimant must have a physical, intellectual, or psychiatric impairment that prevents them from working.\n2. The impairment must be permanent and have persisted for more than 2 years.\n3. Alternatively, the claimant may meet manifest eligibility criteria, such as being permanently blind.\n\nAdditionally, some individuals may be required to participate in a Program of Support (POS) unless they meet certain medical rules or have a specific impairment rating [Source 1][Source 4][Source 5][Source 6]. \n\nFor more detailed information, you can visit the Services Australia website or contact them directly.","sources":[{"index":1,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-12--co029-2601.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2025-12/co029-2601.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.20686459907934468},{"index":2,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-03--co029-2503.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2025-03/co029-2503.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2471344623995621},{"index":3,"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2023-10--aus140-2310nz.pdf.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/sites/default/files/2023-10/aus140-2310nz.pdf","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.29339147227037005},{"index":4,"file":"payments/who-can-get-disability-support-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-disability-support-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.30003253998896573},{"index":5,"file":"general/program-support-for-disability-support-pension.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/program-support-for-disability-support-pension","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3146460706263408},{"index":6,"file":"general/get-centrelink-payment.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/get-centrelink-payment","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.3350189601917966},{"index":7,"file":"payments/who-can-get-utilities-allowance.md","url":"https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/who-can-get-utilities-allowance","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.33711417882190503},{"index":8,"file":"general/income-and-assets-tests-for-disability-suppor